cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with distributed computation of statistical estimations of matrix products, which is a problem in distributed systems. Therefore, cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) as it discusses communication cost and number of rounds of communication. The problem is related to set-intersection join problem in databases, which falls under cs.DB (Databases) and cs.DC (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with statistical estimation, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics, falling under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
